node.text:
Happy Wednesday!
⠀
Your life coach & ambassador @daria_tsvenger is here 👐
⠀
Today I interviewed @aliyagrig - founder of @humancosmosapp - we talked about:
⠀
1. The power of consistency.
2. What it takes to support a person (and yourself) experiencing a mental health challenge.
3. Why we shouldn’t label ourselves.
4. How to love ourselves and why do we need it.
⠀
See you next Wednesday on our weekly LIVE ☀️

node.text:
Every day, I’m suffering, suffering 🥺

Toady I’ll try something new. I’ll reach past the suffering and into the healing. Th is feeling is temporary and I’ll replace it with feelings of gratitude and grace. 

It’s hard, but I can do it! - @therealjoirizarry 

@therapymemequeen

Any questions? Leave them below ⬇️⬇️⬇️

Can’t wait-super humbled and excited! 

Joining? 

XO, Dr. Jen

I would dance like no one was watching or be  worried that I looked silly or awkward.

Maybe I would write that cookbook and not care if even one was not sold. 

Maybe I would just live life and get shit done with no remorse. - @therealjoirizarry

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on July 16, 2021 tagging @brianisze. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Johnny Blasé @BrianlsZe Give yourself permission not to be accessible at all times. Ignore that voicemail. Leave that message on read. Turn off your phone. Don't answer emails. Destroy your SIM card. Burn your house down. Disappear under mysterious circumstances.'.

node.text:
Yesterday was the day. We didn’t literally burn 🔥 the house down, but we did disappear. We needed a social break. 

When the days get tough y’all give yourself some grace and empathy.  Stop 🛑 be so easily accessible. Live in the literal moment and push aside the stuff that’s trying to grab your attention unnecessarily. I have an email trick where I only look at emails every two hours. I answer what I can for thirty minutes and then i go back to my regular work that needs my attention now. It took a while for me to not want the immediacy of answering as they come through, but now I’m not distracted by a bunch of little things all the time and am more efficient in life in general. 

While it’s ok for you to disappear for a while, please don’t burn 🔥 your house down. 🤭 - @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @brianisze 
.
.
.
